- Can you check if we are still align with design principle "Nodics is an enterprise application platform and application factory, designed to let teams build large, customizable business systems without modifying the core framework. The core rule is: capabilities are sacred, implementations are negotiable. Every feature must respect the layered module hierarchy, where framework modules provide default behavior and project/environment/server/node modules can override schemas, services, routers, pipelines, data, tests, configuration, and runtime behavior without changing out-of-the-box Nodics code. Nothing should be hardcoded to a specific project like kickoff; behavior must come from active modules, configuration, tenant context, schema definitions, and runtime governance. Generated artifacts must be recreated from source definitions during build and cleaned safely during clean. Security, access control, validation, audit, rollback, diagnostics, and test coverage are not optional add-ons; they are platform contracts. Any new code should preserve multi-tenancy, modular deployment, runtime configurability, traceability, and backward compatibility while making the system cleaner, safer, and easier to customize." do validated end to end.
